qas.question: What notable shop is located in a grade II listed building?
In what year was Pannier Market finished?
What is Plymouth's national rank in retail floorspace?
What notable location was named a grade II listed building in 1998?
What was the cost to restore Tinside Pool?

context: Plymouth has a post-war shopping area in the city centre with substantial pedestrianisation. At the west end of the zone inside a grade II listed building is the <a0_0>Pannier Market<a0_0/> that was completed in <a1_0>1959<a1_0/> – pannier meaning "basket" from French, so it translates as "basket market". In terms of retail floorspace, Plymouth is ranked in the top five in the South West, and <a2_0>29th<a2_0/> nationally. Plymouth was one of the first ten British cities to trial the new Business Improvement District initiative. The <a3_0>Tinside Pool<a3_0/> is situated at the foot of the Hoe and became a grade II listed building in 1998 before being restored to its 1930s look for <a4_0>£3.4 million<a4_0/>.
